-- Orascom's Algeria Unit Has Difficulty Buying SIM Cards, El Khabar Reports
-- Alaa Shahine
-- 2010-08-02T09:05:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/orascom-s-algeria-unit-has-difficulty-buying-sim-cards-el-khabar-reports.html

          
          
              Orascom Telecom Holding SAE’s unit
in Algeria is facing difficulties buying SIM cards because the
central bank has frozen its accounts and money transfers, El
Khabar newspaper reported today, citing unidentified people.  
 Orascom’s Chief Executive Officer Khaled Bichara and the
company’s spokeswoman, Manal Abdel Hamid, didn’t answer phone
calls from Bloomberg News in Cairo today. Officials at the
Algerian central bank were not immediately available for
comment.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
